article.headline: South Florida 79, Fla. International 50
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- McHugh Mattis had 22 points, 14 rebounds and five blocked shots to lead South Florida to a 79-50 victory over Florida International Tuesday. Melvyn Richardson finished with a career-high 15 points and nine rebounds, and Melvin Buckley scored 15 for South Florida (3-0). Elvis Lora and Johwen Villegas each scored 12 points for Florida International (2-3). Mattis scored eight consecutive points during a 17-4 run that put the South Florida ahead by 19 midway through the first half. The lead peaked at 33 on a twisting layup by senior walk-on Eddie Lovett with 1:22 remaining in the game. South Florida hit nine of its first 10 shots from the field, leading to 71-percent accuracy and a 43-27 lead at the end of the first half.
